<br>
<br>
When AA skills were first introduced, focus as well as crits were both applied to the base damage of the spell, ie:  1120 base damage = ((1120*1.2) * 1.5) =  2016 max crit with 50% crit and 20% focus. <br>
The link you followed refers to the change where focus is no longer added to the base damage before the crit is calculated, resulting in lower max damage, ie (1120 *0.2) + (1120 * 2 ) =  1904 max crit with 50% crit and 20% focus. <p><a target="new"  HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223351">-=Sage Jakarta Pastythug=-</a><BR>
